Privacy Policy for Meowo
Last updated: March 17, 2026
Meowo (“we”, “us”, or “the bot”) is a fun, cat-themed Discord bot that helps communities track activity in a wholesome way. We take your privacy seriously even if we’re mostly made of catnip and meows.
1. Information We Collect
We only collect the absolute minimum needed to run the bot:

Your Discord User ID (a number, never your username or tag unless you run /profile)
Meow Level & XP you earn by chatting
Meow Streak data (last day you sent “meow” and current streak length)
Voice channel time (total minutes/hours spent in any voice channel — this is what powers the Unemployment tracker)
Server ID where the commands are used (only for configuration like streak channel)

We do not collect:

Message content
Voice chat audio
IP addresses
Any personal information (age, email, real name, etc.)

2. How We Use Your Data

To calculate and display your Meow Level, profile, leaderboard, streak, and unemployment stats
To keep your daily streak alive (or sadly reset it)
To show the server’s top meow-ers and top couch cats
To let server admins manage the bot (e.g. set streak channel)

3. Data Storage
All data is stored securely on our servers for as long as your server has the bot. If the bot is removed from a server, your data for that server is automatically deleted within 30 days.
4. Data Sharing
We do not sell, rent, or share your data with any third parties.
The only exception is Discord itself (we use the Discord API to read basic information like when you send “meow” or join a voice channel).
5. Your Rights
You can:

Check all your data with /profile or /unemployment
Ask any server admin to run a data deletion request
Contact us directly (see below) to request complete deletion of your data across all servers

6. Contact
If you have any privacy questions, send a DM to the bot owner or email:
meowo.privacy@gmail.com
(We’ll reply within 48 hours, usually faster because we’re cats and we’re curious.)
By using Meowo, you agree to this Privacy Policy.
